text: Alacrity (meaning "eagerness, liveliness, enthusiasm, or promptness, speed") may refer to: * HMS Alacrity, various Royal Navy ships * USS Alacrity, several US Navy ships * SS Alacrity (1893), a tugboat (originally named Jean Bart) used by the Royal Australian Navy in the First World War * Operation Alacrity, a 1943 Second World War operation involving the occupation of leased air and naval bases in the Azores
title: Alacrity
